1
00:00:04,402 --> 00:00:07,083
What are the ten fetters?

2
00:00:10,528 --> 00:00:19,114
To understand the ten fetters you've got to have understood or know about the different paths and fruits.

3
00:00:21,437 --> 00:00:34,189
The way the Buddha said that people develop spiritually and there are four levels of for want of a better word four levels of deep insight

4
00:00:34,642 --> 00:01:02,049
four levels of consciousness meaning four levels in a change in the way we see things so according to his understanding when we when we begin to see things through the three characteristics of existence when we see things are transient when we see things are not substantial not self

5
00:01:02,805 --> 00:01:23,067
And when we see how we cause ourselves suffering by having a wrong relationship of indulging in pleasure and running away from pain, when we see that, then there's a shift in the way that we relate to the world.

6
00:01:24,930 --> 00:01:29,454
And these three shifts are called the Magga Paula, path and fruit.

7
00:01:31,561 --> 00:01:36,149
So some of you will know it, but I'll just sort of go through them just in case some people don't.

8
00:01:36,489 --> 00:01:38,772
The first one is called Sotapanna.

9
00:01:39,114 --> 00:01:40,236
It means stream entrance.

10
00:01:41,498 --> 00:01:45,144
The second one is known as Sakadagami, once returner.

11
00:01:45,825 --> 00:01:49,230
The third one is Anagami, a non-returner.

12
00:01:49,572 --> 00:01:52,557
And finally there's Arahant, a fully enlightened being.

13
00:01:54,376 --> 00:01:57,781
So the Buddha gives us some images to work with.

14
00:01:57,801 --> 00:02:10,580
He says that when somebody has the first insight into Nibbana, the stream entrant, the one who enters into the spiritual stream and is coming out of samsara, they've found the way out basically.

15
00:02:12,584 --> 00:02:15,147
When you have the first insight, it's like a flash of lightning.

16
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:22,560
So the flash of lightning means that you see everything but you've only seen it for a moment.

17
00:02:23,872 --> 00:02:32,906
So you actually know what the truth is, what Nibbana is, but it's just been that very sharp insight.

18
00:02:35,990 --> 00:02:42,960
The second one, the once-returner, is the one who sees things in a full starry night.

19
00:02:44,581 --> 00:02:48,548
The non-returner sees things, he says, as if it's a full moon.

20
00:02:50,198 --> 00:02:55,086
Even here the full moon can be bright, but those of you who've been to the East know that you can really see colours.

21
00:02:55,105 --> 00:02:56,147
I mean, it's very bright.

22
00:02:57,129 --> 00:03:07,127
But you don't get to see things like the noonday sun until you're fully enlightened.

23
00:03:11,697 --> 00:03:19,909
There's also a teaching about what happens to a person and how long the training is after they've had these insights.

24
00:03:20,191 --> 00:03:27,663
So a Sotapanna, a Shri Mentor is said to have to come back as a human being seven times before they get out of the problem.

25
00:03:29,725 --> 00:03:34,413
A once returner is exactly that, comes back once.

26
00:03:35,727 --> 00:03:46,540
And the non-returner is someone who achieves that third level here, but doesn't have to come back to this realm of existence and works out the rest of their problems in a much better place.

27
00:03:49,144 --> 00:03:55,793
So those are your four levels of noble insight.

28
00:03:56,514 --> 00:03:57,414
Four levels.

29
00:04:04,887 --> 00:04:08,211
I'll give you one more image that he talks about which is rather interesting.

30
00:04:09,252 --> 00:04:18,324
He says that people who don't know the Dharma, who are stuck in delusion, are like people who are swimming underwater and have no clue where they're going.

31
00:04:20,267 --> 00:04:29,459
The trainee is someone who keeps bobbing up and just getting their head above water so they've got some idea as to where they might be going.

32
00:04:32,444 --> 00:04:35,468
The sodapana, the stream entrant, is one who's treading water.

33
00:04:35,949 --> 00:04:37,651
That's rather interesting.

34
00:04:37,672 --> 00:04:38,413
Treading water.

35
00:04:39,935 --> 00:04:43,500
The sakadagami is swimming, hell-bent for the shore.

36
00:04:46,064 --> 00:04:51,432
The anagami, the non-returner, is actually standing on the shore, on the shoreline.

37
00:04:52,113 --> 00:04:55,158
And the arahat has found his seat on the island.

38
00:04:57,021 --> 00:04:59,245
That's another little image that he tells us.

39
00:05:00,035 --> 00:05:04,819
There's another one which comes from the general tradition of spirituality about the mountain.

40
00:05:04,939 --> 00:05:08,805
So if you think about it, the higher you go, the more you see.

41
00:05:08,884 --> 00:05:14,471
But you don't get to see the full thing until you get to the top.

42
00:05:14,490 --> 00:05:17,713
You never get to see what's on the other side of the mountain until you're at the top.

43
00:05:18,896 --> 00:05:27,644
So something happens at the state of full enlightenment which is obviously quite a quantum leap.

44
00:05:29,379 --> 00:05:35,329
And that's the suggestion between a full moon and the noonday sun.

45
00:05:35,348 --> 00:05:39,214
So what is it that these people see to make them ennobled, you see?

46
00:05:39,694 --> 00:05:41,877
They have insights into these three characteristics.

47
00:05:43,060 --> 00:05:52,494
So the more you see transience, the more you see impermanence, then the less attached you are, the less suffering there is.

48
00:05:52,514 --> 00:05:58,543
The more you see how the psychology of seeking happiness in this world, real happiness,

49
00:05:59,653 --> 00:06:01,877
leads only to dissatisfaction.

50
00:06:02,596 --> 00:06:04,158
Then, of course, you come off that drug.

51
00:06:04,178 --> 00:06:06,401
You come off the addiction of sensual pleasure.

52
00:06:07,882 --> 00:06:10,665
Stop running away from just the pain of living.

53
00:06:13,589 --> 00:06:14,771
Sickness, old age and death.

54
00:06:16,673 --> 00:06:23,000
And the more you see that this body, this personality, is not me.

55
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:23,721
It's not a me.

56
00:06:23,761 --> 00:06:24,521
It's not a person.

57
00:06:25,023 --> 00:06:26,584
It's just a conditioned state.

58
00:06:26,625 --> 00:06:27,906
It's just an energy form.

59
00:06:30,805 --> 00:07:00,305
see we know that say looking at those flowers we know that matter matter itself is just energy it's just you know a swirl of subatomic activity they don't even talk about these days they don't even talk about atoms or something still they just talk about energy forms don't they so that even though at our level of perception they are real things they're real colour and they've got a feel about them

60
00:07:01,146 --> 00:07:07,994
When you drop down to a deeper reality about the way the material world is, then all that disappears.

61
00:07:08,014 --> 00:07:09,514
It's just a fuzz of just energy.

62
00:07:11,898 --> 00:07:13,199
So it's the same with this body.

63
00:07:14,319 --> 00:07:19,165
It feels real enough when you get your finger trapped in the door.

64
00:07:19,185 --> 00:07:20,446
And the same with the personality.

65
00:07:20,466 --> 00:07:23,288
It feels real enough when you're depressed or when you're happy.

66
00:07:23,949 --> 00:07:25,812
But it's just energy.

67
00:07:28,353 --> 00:07:31,137
Now, there are two

68
00:07:31,841 --> 00:07:36,069
Parts to becoming one of these noble people.

69
00:07:36,891 --> 00:07:42,300
The first part is called Magga and the second part is called Palla.

70
00:07:43,442 --> 00:07:44,944
Magga is entering into it.

71
00:07:45,586 --> 00:07:50,293
So the insight is what makes you enter into that level of consciousness.

72
00:07:51,415 --> 00:07:55,101
But the fruit of it is the falling away of fetters.

73
00:07:55,702 --> 00:07:56,904
Falling away of the fetters.

74
00:07:58,252 --> 00:08:07,504
And sanyojana, which is the word that fetter is describing, we get the word yoke from it, yoga, yoja, that which binds, that which holds.

75
00:08:07,946 --> 00:08:09,427
And sam is just a strengthener.

76
00:08:09,949 --> 00:08:11,992
So it's something that really binds you.

77
00:08:14,915 --> 00:08:15,956
And there are ten of these.

78
00:08:16,879 --> 00:08:21,105
And as you go up the different paths, the fetters drop away.

79
00:08:23,548 --> 00:08:26,552
And the definition of nibbana is unbinding.

80
00:08:26,572 --> 00:08:26,773
Unbinding.

81
00:08:27,766 --> 00:08:29,869
It's a process of unbinding.

82
00:08:31,851 --> 00:08:32,852
So what are the fetters?

83
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:38,140
The first one is sakkayaditi.

84
00:08:39,482 --> 00:08:44,389
It's the belief in the body or the personality as me and mine.

85
00:08:46,392 --> 00:08:55,225
So there's something about an experience of anicca dukkha anatta, transience, suffering or dissatisfaction and not-self.

86
00:08:55,812 --> 00:09:06,168
which allows that person to see that they are not this body, they are not this personality, they're not emotions, they're not thoughts.

87
00:09:06,187 --> 00:09:11,475
So they've experienced something beyond that, beyond something phenomenal.

88
00:09:13,457 --> 00:09:18,365
So that goes, but don't think that it's thereby entirely destroyed.

89
00:09:19,447 --> 00:09:23,153
You see, what's happened is that the belief in it has gone.

90
00:09:23,774 --> 00:09:50,254
I liken it to the leaving of mother some psychologists say up until about the fourth month there's no differentiation between the baby and mother it's all one thing in fact there's a baby in the world but specifically a baby and mother and then suddenly or at some point

91
00:09:50,690 --> 00:09:52,051
mother becomes other.

92
00:09:52,692 --> 00:10:00,701
It's like it sort of looms out of this me as something other than me.

93
00:10:00,721 --> 00:10:03,123
And that's your first what's known as object relations.

94
00:10:04,585 --> 00:10:07,628
So that's the first leaf taking.

95
00:10:07,648 --> 00:10:13,354
Now how long it takes to get rid of mother?

96
00:10:13,374 --> 00:10:13,494
Eh?

97
00:10:14,615 --> 00:10:15,196
My God.

98
00:10:16,937 --> 00:10:20,562
So you see our binding to our mother is very deep.

99
00:10:22,852 --> 00:10:30,160
So letting go of this body, letting go of this mind, letting go of these emotions is a very long process of leave-taking.

100
00:10:31,061 --> 00:10:35,846
But what the Sotapanna has seen, at least, is that they are not that.

101
00:10:36,427 --> 00:10:40,650
That's a very important little insight.

102
00:10:40,671 --> 00:10:49,080
We get hints of that when, in our meditation, we experience an emotion as something objective within us.

103
00:10:52,654 --> 00:11:01,465
When you become the observer and you feel you're looking at an emotion, experiencing an emotion as if it's not me, not mine.

104
00:11:03,826 --> 00:11:04,207
Correct?

105
00:11:05,168 --> 00:11:08,272
Correct.

106
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:18,484
So that's the sakkayaditi, that's destroying or taking away the fundamental belief that this personality, this body is me.

107
00:11:19,524 --> 00:11:20,586
That's the first thing that goes.

108
00:11:27,501 --> 00:11:31,327
The next one is vichikicca, doubt.

109
00:11:31,347 --> 00:11:45,150
So obviously, if someone has experienced the ultimate truth, nibbana, then obviously all doubt in the Buddha's teaching goes, because now they know for themselves by their own personal experience.

110
00:11:46,432 --> 00:11:48,836
And having done so, they also know the way.

111
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:52,462
So I liken it to somebody...

112
00:11:52,797 --> 00:12:19,006
wandering around in a swamp or something and suddenly through the trees through the swamp and all that they see the top of the mountain so now they've still got a load of swamp to go through but at least they know where they're going and there's no doubt that there is a mountain and there's no doubt that there's a way out of this problem so doubt in the Buddha's teaching disappears

113
00:12:22,548 --> 00:12:24,409
The third one is rather interesting.

114
00:12:25,971 --> 00:12:28,014
Silabata Paramāsa.

115
00:12:28,033 --> 00:12:31,457
It's the recognition of wrong rites and rituals.

116
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:40,386
It's understanding that the path to become enlightened has virtually nothing to do with rites and rituals.

117
00:12:41,989 --> 00:12:50,418
No matter how many times you bow to the Buddha, light candles, repeat your Om Mani Padme Hams.

118
00:12:50,638 --> 00:12:51,558
Nothing to do with it.

119
00:12:54,408 --> 00:13:21,461
if we could just hold the line of pure meditation that's enough there's an interesting scripture where some young monks go to the elders and they say how did you become enlightened and the split even then is between those monks and nuns who like to live completely by themselves in the forest

120
00:13:21,965 --> 00:13:29,392
And those who were much more into towns and the study and all that, remembering, in those days, rote learning.

121
00:13:31,854 --> 00:13:41,543
So those, it was Cassifer, the very great ascetic, who said that you have to keep the rule very fiercely.

122
00:13:42,604 --> 00:13:45,866
You must keep the rule about renunciation.

123
00:13:46,368 --> 00:13:48,850
You must live out in the forest and you must meditate.

124
00:13:50,264 --> 00:14:19,191
and Sariputta who was the considered to be the general of the Dharma second only to the Buddha in understanding said you must understand you must learn what the Buddha's teaching is and you must meditate so this troop of young monks went off to the Buddha and they said to him we've asked so and so this we've asked so and so that and we get these answers what do you think you see and he says well all teachers will bring you the way they came they'll bring you the way they came

125
00:14:19,423 --> 00:14:22,769
So they said, Lord, what is your teaching?

126
00:14:23,028 --> 00:14:35,749
And his reply was, Meditate, meditate, meditate.

127
00:14:35,769 --> 00:14:46,345
So if we can bear the horror of sitting and walking and continuing to meditate all the time, then that would be the most direct way.

128
00:14:48,047 --> 00:14:48,687
However,

129
00:14:50,812 --> 00:14:53,054
That doesn't mean to say we can't have rituals.

130
00:14:53,115 --> 00:14:56,119
It doesn't mean to say you can't have other practices, you see.

131
00:14:56,259 --> 00:15:04,389
But there's an understanding in the stream entrant that they are not material, directly material to the path of enlightenment.

132
00:15:06,432 --> 00:15:08,154
So I mean they're skillful means, you know.

133
00:15:08,315 --> 00:15:20,750
I mean it's a skillful thing to say, repeat a phrase, say a loving kindness phrase, may all beings be happy, than it is to let the mind wander off to Machu Picchu or

134
00:15:22,721 --> 00:15:23,844
Gold Coast or something.

135
00:15:24,807 --> 00:15:24,986
See?

136
00:15:25,368 --> 00:15:27,392
So at least it's a skillful means.

137
00:15:27,412 --> 00:15:29,235
A skillful means.

138
00:15:29,255 --> 00:15:30,177
So that's what drops.

139
00:15:30,217 --> 00:15:33,304
Now in the Buddha's day, remember, there were all sorts of very strange things.

140
00:15:33,325 --> 00:15:36,291
Remember, we're talking about medieval and pre-medieval times.

141
00:15:36,773 --> 00:15:42,063
And a lot of people, even these days, believe that ritual has some sort of...

142
00:15:43,647 --> 00:16:00,120
efficacy about it in itself which brings about some form of enlightenment for instance there were times in those times people thought that if you stood in the Ganges just stood there the purifying water of the Ganges would take all your bad karma away

143
00:16:09,549 --> 00:16:20,846
there was understanding that somehow you had to go through enormous suffering to sort of get rid of suffering, sort of mortification.

144
00:16:22,208 --> 00:16:26,735
Like if you, on a very hot day, you'd build a fire and sit next to the fire.

145
00:16:28,698 --> 00:16:31,482
And somehow that had this purifying effect.

146
00:16:32,524 --> 00:16:34,347
You know, the purifying nature of fire.

147
00:16:34,567 --> 00:16:37,211
So you can see it's around superstition and around

148
00:16:37,477 --> 00:16:39,400
wrong beliefs, things like that.

149
00:16:41,003 --> 00:16:42,445
So that's the third thing that goes.

150
00:16:42,684 --> 00:16:47,350
So in other words, for the Sotapanna, the stream entrant, their practice is very direct.

151
00:16:47,490 --> 00:16:48,773
They know where they're going, you see.

152
00:16:48,793 --> 00:16:53,460
They don't get pulled off and here and there with all sorts of stuff, you know.

153
00:16:54,400 --> 00:17:00,729
I Ching, astrology, I don't know.

154
00:17:00,749 --> 00:17:04,134
So then the next movement is to the once returner.

155
00:17:04,595 --> 00:17:07,198
And what these people break is

156
00:17:07,954 --> 00:17:25,579
Or they undermine the two next things, which are kamarāga, translates as indulgence in pleasure, and vyapāda, hatred, aversion.

157
00:17:25,601 --> 00:17:27,423
So those two things go.

158
00:17:27,903 --> 00:17:37,017
Now, if you think about it, you see, from an ego point of view, from this ego level, from this self level, which believes that

159
00:17:37,637 --> 00:17:38,538
This is what it is.

160
00:17:38,578 --> 00:17:40,340
You've got to make the most of this now.

161
00:17:40,981 --> 00:17:43,163
There's only two ways to behave.

162
00:17:44,246 --> 00:17:59,663
Wherever happiness seems to come to you, whether it's pleasure, straightforward pleasure, you know, bangers and mash and beans, or whether it's something, a relationship or music or even spiritual delight.

163
00:18:00,402 --> 00:18:08,936
From the self point of view, if that's what happiness is going to be, there's going to be a clinging to it, a wanting it, a holding on to it, a wanting to develop it.

164
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:20,676
And if anything is in any way oppressive or seems to undermine happiness, any form of dissatisfaction, then there's going to be an effort to push it away.

165
00:18:22,701 --> 00:18:25,566
So that's the only way a real self can behave.

166
00:18:26,103 --> 00:18:30,409
You don't have an option when you're down at the level of me and mine.

167
00:18:32,633 --> 00:18:38,040
But now, when somebody has so broken the idea of me and mine, they're not playing that game anymore.

168
00:18:39,522 --> 00:18:41,385
See, that game is undermined.

169
00:18:41,645 --> 00:18:45,391
It doesn't mean to say that they won't indulge and they won't get angry and all that sort of stuff.

170
00:18:45,832 --> 00:18:49,678
But it's like the heaviness has gone.

171
00:18:51,359 --> 00:18:54,625
And it's only at the third stage that these two are completely undermined.

172
00:18:55,397 --> 00:18:57,619
And that's why there's a non-returner, you see.

173
00:18:57,901 --> 00:19:05,528
They don't come back because there's nothing here attracting them anymore.

174
00:19:05,548 --> 00:19:06,829
However, there's still attachment.

175
00:19:07,770 --> 00:19:15,519
And the attachment now is to the more finer mental states and more finer realms.

176
00:19:16,319 --> 00:19:19,383
And these are to do with the absorptions that we practice.

177
00:19:19,943 --> 00:19:20,964
Or you can practice.

178
00:19:22,165 --> 00:19:24,949
So these are the rupa and the arupa.

179
00:19:26,953 --> 00:19:30,078
So what do we mean by that?

180
00:19:30,239 --> 00:19:45,381
We mean that when somebody practices absorption meditations, ecstatic meditations, what they come to understand, what they realize is that they can create beautiful mental states independent of the world.

181
00:19:47,384 --> 00:19:53,231
So when we practice loving kindness, for instance, and we just put that phrase in our hearts, may all beings be happy, you see,

182
00:19:54,055 --> 00:19:55,115
May all beings be happy.

183
00:19:55,517 --> 00:19:58,141
And we begin to feel the joy.

184
00:19:58,181 --> 00:20:00,243
That's just created by us, within us.

185
00:20:03,428 --> 00:20:07,753
So this releases you from dependence on sausage and mash.

186
00:20:09,036 --> 00:20:11,439
Beans.

187
00:20:11,940 --> 00:20:13,342
You don't need the world out there.

188
00:20:13,382 --> 00:20:16,205
You can just engender this loveliness within yourself.

189
00:20:18,868 --> 00:20:19,269
And

190
00:20:19,739 --> 00:20:27,946
The progress of that gets very fine until you come to a very fine place of absolute equanimity where there's not even an object.

191
00:20:30,390 --> 00:20:35,454
And those who experience these things always say that this is the highest happiness, not something else.

192
00:20:37,016 --> 00:20:41,621
All the way up that chain, all the way up those degrees of ecstasy to pure equanimity.

193
00:20:42,201 --> 00:20:46,506
Those people who have experienced these things always say, well, this is the highest happiness.

194
00:20:46,772 --> 00:20:47,574
Not the other one.

195
00:20:48,134 --> 00:20:50,519
Everything begins to feel more and more gross.

196
00:20:52,663 --> 00:20:55,608
So that attachment doesn't go.

197
00:20:55,648 --> 00:21:01,980
Those two attachments don't go until you're fully enlightened.

198
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,243
The other thing that doesn't go is conceit.

199
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:10,434
So the I, the me stays right to the bitter end.

200
00:21:14,144 --> 00:21:18,951
So don't think at any moment that you will not suffer from conceit and arrogance.

201
00:21:19,951 --> 00:21:22,355
It will stay with you to the bitter end.

202
00:21:25,358 --> 00:21:27,962
The other thing is restlessness, which is interesting.

203
00:21:28,804 --> 00:21:29,384
Restlessness.

204
00:21:29,766 --> 00:21:34,813
And although it doesn't say so, in my own personal understanding, it must also include sloth.

205
00:21:35,574 --> 00:21:38,817
Because they're just two energy forms, one going out, one coming in.

206
00:21:39,355 --> 00:21:44,701
So, so long as there's an impurity in the heart, there's going to be that shaking, that restlessness.

207
00:21:46,763 --> 00:21:57,217
So our struggle with sloth, torpor and restlessness must also be carried on to the bitter end.

208
00:21:57,237 --> 00:22:01,122
And finally, of course, what is completely undercut is ignorance.

209
00:22:01,142 --> 00:22:02,163
That's the last fetter.

210
00:22:02,884 --> 00:22:04,826
Ignorance here means don't know.

211
